Lastly, you want to generate text to represent this countdown value. 

You can interrogate the `Duration` objects for its parts, a number of generic 24-hour days (not related to the calendar), hours, minutes, seconds, and nanos. Use the various `to…Part` methods on the [`Duration`][7] class. 

    long days = duration.toDaysPart() ;
    int hours = duration.toHoursPart() ;
    int minutes = duration.toMinutesPart() ;
    int seconds = duration.toSecondsPart() ;

