answers.body_markdown:
Seems you are missing the template named `home`. You need to create this template and store it under `\src\main\resources\templates`
The template is a html file to which you are returning your response from spring to. It should be something like this:


    project-directory
    -&gt;src
        -&gt;main
            -&gt;java-&gt;com-&gt;...etc
            -&gt;resources
                -&gt;static
                -&gt;templates
                    home.html
                    other_file.html
                application.properties
          
        -&gt;test

Also stop using specific versions. Use this:

    &lt;dependency&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-starter-data-jpa&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;

    &lt;dependency&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-starter-web&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;

Also rollback to TomCat 9 as 10 is not supported.

    &lt;dependency&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.tomcat.embed&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;tomcat-embed-jasper&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;version&gt;9.0.19&lt;/version&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;

&lt;br&gt;

You can get these dependencies from [The MVN Repository][1]


  [1]: https://mvnrepository.com/

